-- в”Ђв”Ђ Misago в”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђв”Ђ
UPDATE tools SET
  short_description = COALESCE($q$Misago is a free, open-source, Django and React-based forum application designed for building fast, scalable, and modern online communities.$q$, short_description),
  pricing_model = COALESCE($q$Open Source$q$, pricing_model),
  starting_price = COALESCE($q$Free$q$, starting_price),
  founded_year = COALESCE(2013, founded_year),
  company_size = COALESCE(NULL, company_size),
  headquarters = COALESCE(NULL, headquarters),
  languages = ARRAY[$q$English$q$]::text[],
  seo_title = COALESCE($q$Misago Review 2026: Features, Pricing and Alternatives$q$, seo_title),
  seo_meta_description = COALESCE($q$Misago review: a free, open-source Django and React forum application for building fast, modern online communities. Features, pricing, and alternatives.$q$, seo_meta_description),
  llm_readable_summary = COALESCE($q$Misago is a free and open-source forum application created by developer RafaЕ‚ PitoЕ„, with the project's earliest source available under the rafalp/Misago GitHub repository dating back to around 2013. It is built on Python's Django web framework for the backend and JavaScript/React for the frontend, positioning it as a modern, actively developed alternative to other stand-alone forum software such as Discourse, phpBB, or Invision Community. Misago is designed to be fast, scalable, and responsive, targeting communities that want a self-hosted discussion board rather than a hosted SaaS product. Core functionality includes user account management with registration, profile customization, avatars, password recovery, and OAuth login integration with more than 50 third-party providers including Google, Facebook, GitHub, and Steam. Content features support Markdown and BBCode formatting, threaded discussions, post attachments with automatic thumbnail generation, full edit history with revision tracking, and a best-answer marking system for question-and-answer style categories. Community organization is handled through an unlimited number and depth of categories and subcategories, letting administrators structure large or niche communities. Moderation tooling includes a comprehensive moderation queue, post approval workflows, user and content management tools, a banning system that can target usernames, email addresses, or IP addresses, and granular permission controls tied to user roles and groups. As free open-source software, Misago carries no licensing fee: operators install and run their own instance on their own servers, meaning the only costs are hosting infrastructure and any custom development or support they choose to arrange, in contrast to commercial enterprise forum platforms like Jive, Lithium, or Telligent, which historically have run into thousands of dollars per month. The project is distributed via PyPI as the misago Python package and via its GitHub repository, and community discussion and support happen on the official Misago Project Forums (misago-project.org), which itself runs on Misago as a demonstration of the software. Misago's target audience includes developers, open-source communities, niche hobbyist or professional forums, and organizations that want full control over their forum's code, data, and hosting rather than relying on a third-party-hosted community platform. Its main competitors include Discourse (the most prominent modern open-source forum alternative, available both self-hosted and hosted), phpBB, NodeBB, Flarum, and legacy forum software like vBulletin, with Misago differentiating itself through its Django/Python foundation, React-based modern UI, and fully free and open licensing without a paid hosted tier.$q$, llm_readable_summary),
  status = 'published',
  noindex = false,
  sitemap_eligible = true,
  published_at = COALESCE(published_at, now()),
  updated_at = now()
WHERE id = '2b43eeda-4ceb-459a-a73d-d764275698c6';

